HEADWORD: Spitzenburgh
<hw>Spitz"en*burgh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of red
and yellow apple, of medium size and spicy flavor. It originated at
Newtown, on Long Island.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splanchnapophysis</ent>⟦br⟧
